This paper deals with stochastic convex optimization, a problem that is commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves statistical query algorithms, which are a tool used in theoretical computer science, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The paper also involves optimization, which is a topic studied in cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the paper has implications for machine learning and neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category as well.
